HEADWORD: Haemochromometer
<hw>Haem`o*chro*mom"e*ter</hw>
<pr>(-kr⟦osl⟧*m⟦ocr⟧m"⟦esl⟧*t⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Haemochrome</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>An apparatus for measuring the amount of hemoglobin in
a fluid, by comparing it with a solution of known strength and of normal
color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Haemocyanin</ent>⟦br⟧
